      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "6e6d74465e7b215d",
      "text": "Payment in general, and prices in particular, are characterized by a high degree of [[Information Loss]]: the payer does not provide information on the origin of the money, and the payee is not required to explain what will become of the money. That means that a price-oriented system can function almost without [[Memory]]: we do not remember who executed the payment and why, and who could not execute payment. The payee is immediately free to use the money for any other combination.\n"
